{"lemma":"أَبْلَج","slug":"أَبْلَج","root":"ب.ل.ج","root_slug":"ب-ل-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ل-ج","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","","n3154"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8E%D8%AC"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"bright, serene, clear"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from بَلَجَ (balaja)."},"ipa":["/ʔab.lad͡ʒ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3154","headword_ar":"اَبْلَجُ","root":"blj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a clear, a conspicuous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a white, space between the eyes, not having the eyebrows joined:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having such a space between the eyebrows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not having the eyebrows joined:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a wide space,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a space clear of hair, between the eyebrows:"},{"kind":"text","text":"fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balojaA='u","text_ar":"بَلْجَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bright"},{"kind":"text","text":"of countenance; the Prophet being said by UmmMaabad to have been"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abolaju Alwajohi","text_ar":"اَبْلَجُ الوَجْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; by which she did not mean the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaj","text_ar":"بَلَج"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the eyebrows, for she described him as having joined eyebrows: (A'Obeyd, S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fair, beautiful, and wide in countenance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether long or short: or [alone, or] followed by ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balojN","text_ar":"بَلْجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"open and pleasant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheerful, in countenance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and so ↓ the latter alone: (K:) or ↓ the latter, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"open and pleasant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheerful, in countenance, with beneficence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the former, and ↓ the latter, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baliyjN","text_ar":"بَلِيجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liberal with acts of beneficence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the first, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous, beneficent, and open and pleasant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheerful, in countenance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"although having joined eyebrows. (A, TA.) ―         -b3-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Shining, bright,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shining brightly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to the dawn, or daybreak; (S, A, Msb;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baliyjN","text_ar":"بَلِيجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a thing [of any kind]: (TA:) and the former, anything (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apparent, manifest, evident,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) thus applied to a face, and to the dawn, (TA,) and to the truth, (Msb, TA,) and to an affair or event, or a case, &c. (TA.) It is an act. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balija","text_ar":"بَلِجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaq~u A^abolaju wa AlbaATilu lajolajN","text_ar":"الحَقُّ اَبْلَجُ وَ البَاطِلُ لَجْلَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The truth is apparent, manifest, evident,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and falsity is a cause of embarrassment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hesitation, to the speaker;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, A; *) i. e., the latter is agitated to and fro, without having utterance: (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lj","text_ar":"لج"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the truth is lucid and direct; and falsity is confused and indirect."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in that art.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huj~apN balojaA='u","text_ar":"حُجَّةٌ بَلْجَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A manifest, an evident,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a clear, proof"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"argument."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["ISh","TA","S","K","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}